Key Match Events: The New York Mets defeated the Washington Nationals 10-1 last night.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Washington Nationals had the New York Mets starter Tylor Megill on the ropes in the third inning, putting runners on first and third with no outs, but they could score only one run.
Others: The Washington Nationals finish up their three game series against the New York Mets tonight.
The Washington Nationals will travel to Chicago to face the Chicago Cubs for a four-game series, concluding their final road trip of the 2024 season.
